Title: Beethoven Piano Concerto No1 – Ethan Loch – Royal Scottish National Orchestra
Description:
Beethoven's Piano Concerto No1 conducted by Thomas Søndergård and performed by pianist Ethan Loch and the Royal Scottish National Orchestra. Plus, Ethan Loch performs two of his own compositions as encores. Recorded at The Glasgow Royal Concert Hall on 30 November 2024.

0:00 Movement I: Allegro con brio
19:33 Movement II: Largo
31:11 Movement III: Rondo. Allegro scherzando 
42:43 Encore One: Out of the Darkness
50:25 Encore Two: Melody of Tranquility
.
Watch Ethan Loch: A World of Sound at https://youtu.be/eDlK3Qm1FFE
.
Find out more about the Royal Scottish National Orchestra: https://www.rsno.org.uk/

Title: Mahler Symphony No1 – Thomas Søndergård – Royal Scottish National Orchestra
Description:
Mahler Symphony No1 with Music Director Thomas Søndergård. 

0:30 Movement I: Langsam, Schleppend (Slow, dragging) - Immer sehr gemächlich (Always at a very leisurely pace)
15:45 Movement II: Kräftig bewegt, doch nicht zu schnell (with strong movement, but not too fast) - Trio: Recht gemächlich (Quite leisurely) - Tempo primo
23:25 Movement III: Feierlich und gemessen, ohne zu schleppen (Solemn and measured, without dragging)
34:28 Movement IV: Stürmisch bewegt (Stormy)

If you enjoyed this performance and would like to support the RSNO, please consider donating at https://www.rsno.org.uk/support-us/playyourpart/.

This performance was recorded on Saturday 5 October 2019 at the Glasgow Royal Concert Hall. The concert was dedicated to the RSNO Conductors Circle. Original audio feed courtesy of BBC Radio 3.
